  [warning] Compound assignment repeats `a`
   ╭─[test.lis:4:3]
 3 │   let mut a = 2
 4 │   a *= a * b
   ·   ─────┬────
   ·        ╰── uses `a` twice
 5 │   let _ = a
   ╰────
  help: The `*=` operator already includes `a`, so naming `a` again on the right applies it twice. To apply `b` once, write `a *= b` · code: [lint.misrefactored_assign_op]
